sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1113411
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Targeting sequence for the delivery of the LacZ gene to the Carboxysome
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The large subunits of the RuBisCo was obtained from the pHnCBS1D plasmid (plasmid provided by David Savage, Departments of Molecular & Cell Biology and Chemistry, University of California, Berkeley)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Includes the lacZ gene (BBa_I732005) which encodes for the β-galactosidase attached with a linker (BBa_K105012) to the large subunit of the RuBisCo (BBa_K1113701) under the regulation of the pBad/araC promoter (BBa_I0500) and includes a RBS (BBa_B0034). The construct is for the delivery of the β-galactosidase and test reactions within the carboxysome. Source of this part: The large subunits of the RuBisCo was obtained from the pHnCBS1D plasmid (plasmid provided by David Savage, Departments of Molecular & Cell Biology and Chemistry, University of California, Berkeley)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part it constructed with a mutation in the Prefix (from ???cggccgc??? to ???atacctg???) which erase the NotI restriction site, this modification allow the correct design of primers for Gibson assembly. This part its also constructed on the pSB4K5 standard vector
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Belen Cespedes

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: LacZ
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: PCR amplified and standardized from BL21
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: LacZ encodes beta-galactosidase, an intracellular enzyme that cleaves the disaccharide lactose into glucose and galactose. Beta-galactosidase can also cleaves X-gal and ONPG into colorful products.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Zhan Jian

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K105012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Oligos with a yeast optimized coding for the peptide GENLYFQSGG have been ordered <br\n> The amino acide sequence corresponds to the interdomaine linker of xxx. ''paper''
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This is a 10 amino acides long linker peptide which can be used to join protein domains together in a flexible way. So fusion proteins with variable DNA-binding and activation or repression domains might be assembled.
<br\n>
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
To enable the fusion with other domains in frame the vector of this BioBrick has no base pair in between the restriction side and the BioBrick. Furthermore, this coding sequence does not include a start codon.
For more information about this issus, see:
Phillips, I.E. and Silver, P.A. "A new Biobrick Assembly Strategy Designed for Facile Protein Engineering."
DSpace http://hdl.handle.net/1721.1/32535 (2006).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Manuel Gersbacher, Katja Karstens
